WEBVTT

00:01.202 --> 00:03.737
-I'm a
once-in-a-generation artist.
-Oh.

00:03.771 --> 00:06.874
Who just got verified
on Twitter, about,
what, nine days ago?

00:06.907 --> 00:09.177
I'm glad you feel good
that a robot told you
you're worth it.

00:09.210 --> 00:10.578
* Hi, I'm Dave *

00:26.127 --> 00:28.229
(odd creaking sound)

00:32.733 --> 00:34.868
(sound repeats)

00:36.304 --> 00:38.806
What the...

00:41.575 --> 00:43.043
Who the hell gave you permission

00:43.077 --> 00:45.113
to monkey around
with my precious volumes?

00:45.146 --> 00:46.547
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

00:46.580 --> 00:47.848
NANDOR:
What has he done now?

00:47.881 --> 00:50.050
He's been monkeying around
with my precious volumes.

00:50.084 --> 00:53.053
-No, I haven't been monkey--
I haven't touched your books.
-Oh, really?

00:53.087 --> 00:55.523
Well, explain this.

00:55.556 --> 00:57.225
Shit, he's taken it up
a notch.

00:57.258 --> 00:58.559
That's worse than before.

00:58.592 --> 01:00.694
Guillermo, why would you
do such a thing?

01:00.728 --> 01:02.696
I didn't do it. I-I haven't even
been in this room.

01:02.730 --> 01:03.931
I wasn't even here.

01:03.964 --> 01:05.099
LASZLO:
Well, you're in there now.

01:05.133 --> 01:06.967
-NADJA: What's going on?
-LASZLO: It's Gizmo.

01:07.000 --> 01:08.636
He's been causing havoc
in the household.

01:08.669 --> 01:11.071
Ooh.

01:11.105 --> 01:12.840
Look. Look.

01:16.510 --> 01:19.447
"Laszlo sucks," backwards.

01:19.480 --> 01:21.149
LASZLO:
Laszlo doesn't suck.

01:21.182 --> 01:23.284
And if he did, he certainly
wouldn't do it backwards.

01:23.317 --> 01:24.285
GUILLERMO:
I didn't write it.

01:24.318 --> 01:26.454
NADJA:
Hmm.

01:26.487 --> 01:27.988
We've got ghosts.

01:28.021 --> 01:29.423
-Bullshit.
-(Nadja groans)

01:29.457 --> 01:32.059
(Laszlo grunts)

01:32.092 --> 01:34.162
("You're Dead"
by Norma Tanega playing)

01:34.195 --> 01:36.730
* Don't sing if you want
to live long *

01:36.764 --> 01:39.167
* They have no use
for your song *

01:39.200 --> 01:41.902
* You're dead, you're dead,
you're dead *

01:41.935 --> 01:44.772
* You're dead
and out of this world *

01:46.307 --> 01:49.343
* Now your hope and compassion
is gone *

01:49.377 --> 01:52.112
* You sold out your dream
to the world *

01:52.146 --> 01:54.448
* Stay dead, stay dead,
stay dead *

01:54.482 --> 01:57.117
* You're dead
and out of this world. *

02:06.560 --> 02:09.029
A ghost is the spirit
of a person who has died,

02:09.062 --> 02:12.200
but still has unfinished
business

02:12.233 --> 02:13.267
on this mortal plane.

02:13.301 --> 02:14.602
There's no such thing
as ghosts.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.103
Okay, here we go again.

02:16.136 --> 02:17.505
My wife comes from
the kind of town

02:17.538 --> 02:19.840
that believes in all this kind
of superstitious nonsense.

02:19.873 --> 02:21.942
She also thinks
goblins are real.

02:21.975 --> 02:24.378
Personally, I'm a man
of science.

02:24.412 --> 02:27.181
All right, then, Dr. Arsehole,
how does your science

02:27.215 --> 02:29.617
-explain what we just saw?
-Now, you see,

02:29.650 --> 02:31.151
it can be one of two things.

02:31.185 --> 02:32.453
One, a mercurical zephyr.

02:32.486 --> 02:34.488
Two, it's a farrago of gasses,

02:34.522 --> 02:36.123
possibly from a peat bog.

02:36.156 --> 02:38.326
Now, if you capture these
and add them together,

02:38.359 --> 02:41.195
-using yellow bile
from a plague victim...
-(hisses)

02:41.229 --> 02:43.531
...you've got what
looks like a ghost.

02:43.564 --> 02:45.533
-But it's science.
-Ooh! (blows raspberry)

02:45.566 --> 02:47.201
NANDOR:
Ghosts are

02:47.235 --> 02:49.203
the stuff of fairy tales.

02:49.237 --> 02:51.472
Stories we tell children
to frighten out

02:51.505 --> 02:54.242
their excess energy
so that they might

02:54.275 --> 02:56.544
-slumber more peacefully.
-GUILLERMO: Huh.

02:58.712 --> 03:00.848
Did you say something?

03:00.881 --> 03:03.351
I'm sorry, vampires are real,
but ghosts are not?

03:03.384 --> 03:07.588
He's heard too many
fairy stories from Nadja.

03:07.621 --> 03:08.722
No, I actually just want
to make sure

03:08.756 --> 03:09.823
we're on the same page.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.892
You know, after years
of working for you,

03:11.925 --> 03:14.262
a known vampire,
I have seen

03:14.295 --> 03:16.264
-werewolves, necromancers...
-(growling)

03:16.297 --> 03:18.065
...a zombie
and several Babadooks,

03:18.098 --> 03:20.200
but a ghost, that's where
we draw the line.

03:20.234 --> 03:22.770
Several?
You saw one Bababook.

03:22.803 --> 03:25.205
-Several Ba--
-Don't exaggerate.

03:26.607 --> 03:28.509
Do I believe in ghosts?
Uh, no.

03:28.542 --> 03:30.110
Color me skeptical.

03:30.143 --> 03:34.582
Um, though, maybe it's ghosts
that are always stealing

03:34.615 --> 03:38.452
that one sock from the dryer.
(laughs)

03:38.486 --> 03:42.189
I've been experimenting
with, uh, humor

03:42.222 --> 03:44.692
to drain energy.

03:44.725 --> 03:47.227
Which reminds me,
does anyone here

03:47.261 --> 03:49.196
have any updog?

03:49.229 --> 03:51.699
Updog?

03:51.732 --> 03:53.534
If I didn't know
what updog was,

03:53.567 --> 03:56.570
I would at least ask-ask me.
(chuckles)

03:58.439 --> 04:03.311
Hey, everybody, look at
my enormous crystal balls.

04:03.344 --> 04:07.247
Maybe these ghosts will
bring with them some updog.

04:07.281 --> 04:11.819
Guillermo, did you get my joke
about my enormous balls?

04:11.852 --> 04:14.254
-I did, Master.
-NADJA: Silence!

04:14.288 --> 04:15.423
The time is nigh.

04:15.456 --> 04:17.325
Everybody join hands.

04:17.358 --> 04:19.159
COLIN:
Sorry if my hands are
a little oily.

04:19.192 --> 04:21.829
It's from my rash cream.

04:21.862 --> 04:24.832
NADJA:
Troubled spirits,
draw ye near.

04:24.865 --> 04:29.269
Uncloak yourselves
and reveal to us your forms

04:29.303 --> 04:30.638
on this terrestrial plane.

04:30.671 --> 04:34.241
I beseech you,
using the ancient words.

04:34.274 --> 04:35.676
'Eye' tis ka lay

04:35.709 --> 04:39.847
ksenikon e patroion,
e pakouston e foraton e keye,

04:39.880 --> 04:41.682
kath-eye-restho hon-'pear'

04:41.715 --> 04:44.117
apokatharet-eye.

04:44.151 --> 04:45.986
(vocalizing)

04:46.019 --> 04:47.521
Mm...

04:47.555 --> 04:49.089
(loud creaking)

04:49.122 --> 04:51.559
(creaking moan echoes)

04:54.294 --> 04:56.864
-Guillermo, did you make a fart?
-No.

04:56.897 --> 04:59.132
I think someone summoned
a breakfast burrito.

04:59.166 --> 05:00.133
Silence!

05:00.167 --> 05:02.269
A spirit is struggling
to be heard.

05:02.302 --> 05:06.106
Is it maybe a spirit
who's struggling with IBS?

05:06.139 --> 05:08.141
(laughter)

05:08.175 --> 05:10.177
You have ruined
the energy of the sÃ©ance

05:10.210 --> 05:13.046
with your toilet potty
poo-poo-mouth humor!

05:13.080 --> 05:16.283
And a price will be paid.
You fools!

05:16.316 --> 05:20.821
Nadja, we were only joking.

05:20.854 --> 05:22.122
Idiots.

05:22.155 --> 05:24.825
(sighs)

05:28.028 --> 05:29.530
(Nadja gasps)

05:32.366 --> 05:33.367
Oh, yes.

05:33.401 --> 05:36.236
Jeff... Jesk.

05:36.269 --> 05:38.005
So you are a ghost now, yes?

05:38.038 --> 05:40.674
My Nadja.

05:40.708 --> 05:42.576
For an eternity,
I have longed to hear

05:42.610 --> 05:45.245
your sweet, angelic voice
say my name again.

05:45.278 --> 05:47.247
Well, it's only been a few
months since you died,

05:47.280 --> 05:50.484
but that's...
Thank you, very nice.

05:50.518 --> 05:52.319
I have missed you so.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.754
Sorry, can I just stop you?

05:53.787 --> 05:55.889
It's really weird
with you down there.

05:55.923 --> 05:57.190
If you could--
Sorry, the head.

05:57.224 --> 05:59.092
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:59.126 --> 06:00.661
-Put it back on the neck.
Sorry, it's just...
-Right, right, right, right.

06:00.694 --> 06:03.063
-Duh. Ew.
-Ugh. (chuckles)

06:03.096 --> 06:04.097
This is better, huh?

06:04.131 --> 06:05.198
So much better.

06:05.232 --> 06:08.602
-Thanks.
-So, Jesk, what can I...

06:08.636 --> 06:11.104
Um, sorry for not taking you
seriously, my darling.

06:11.138 --> 06:13.741
(scoffs) And what do you
think about it now?

06:13.774 --> 06:15.275
What do I think about what?

06:15.308 --> 06:16.544
Jesk, say something.

06:16.577 --> 06:18.712
Hey, thanks for
cutting my head off.

06:18.746 --> 06:21.348
-Again. You dick.
-NADJA: Now, now.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.383
He was just doing
his husbandly duties.

06:23.417 --> 06:25.185
Who are you talking to,
my darling?

06:25.218 --> 06:26.353
Can't you see him?

06:26.386 --> 06:29.356
There's nobody there, my dear.
Are you okay?

06:29.389 --> 06:31.391
-He's sitting right there.
-There's no one there.

06:31.425 --> 06:33.193
-But he's...
-I'll, uh,

06:33.226 --> 06:34.462
just go back inside
and leave you

06:34.495 --> 06:37.064
to, uh, talking to the air.

06:38.666 --> 06:41.301
Shit.

06:41.334 --> 06:43.036
Nandor!

06:43.070 --> 06:45.238
-There's a fucking ghost
on the front lawn.
-What?

06:45.272 --> 06:47.240
-Not you, too.
-I couldn't believe it myself.

06:47.274 --> 06:50.143
But what mine own eyes have
seen, mine own eyes have seen.

06:50.177 --> 06:51.278
I pretended I couldn't see it,

06:51.311 --> 06:53.213
which will give us
the element of surprise.

06:53.246 --> 06:56.216
-Okay. Okay.
-We must act quickly.

06:56.249 --> 06:57.451
Take the large one.

06:57.485 --> 06:58.619
Yes, good idea.

06:58.652 --> 07:00.921
Yeah, that's better.

07:00.954 --> 07:02.823
Right, where's this
fucking ghost?!

07:02.856 --> 07:05.593
(shouting)

07:05.626 --> 07:06.727
JEFF:
...ghost stuff.

07:06.760 --> 07:10.464
Aah! Get ready to swallow
my sword! (grunts)

07:10.498 --> 07:12.533
But it's... What the fuck?

07:18.506 --> 07:20.240
Whoa, shit.

07:20.273 --> 07:22.275
-That's wild.
-Thank you!

07:22.309 --> 07:24.612
-So, this...
-You need to keep
your voice down, otherwise

07:24.645 --> 07:26.647
-that thing will hear us.
-I can hear you.

07:26.680 --> 07:27.981
Now look what you've done.

07:28.015 --> 07:30.017
-What is this gloopy shit?
-Huh.

07:30.050 --> 07:31.451
Looks like ectoplasm.

07:31.485 --> 07:33.821
-Is that right?
-(chuckling): I guess so.

07:33.854 --> 07:37.357
-Is there any in my hair?
-Yeah, yeah. Oh, yeah.

07:37.390 --> 07:38.458
Guillermo, tissue, please.

07:38.492 --> 07:40.528
-COLIN: Quite a bit.
-NANDOR: Fucking guy.

07:40.561 --> 07:41.695
That thing needs to be gone.

07:41.729 --> 07:42.963
He's not going to hurt us.

07:42.996 --> 07:45.533
-You're not going
to hurt them, right?
-No.

07:45.566 --> 07:46.967
I'm not gonna hurt you guys.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.468
-I'm just here
to scare you guys.
-LASZLO: Bollocks.

07:48.502 --> 07:49.970
-Well, we're not scared.
-You should be scared of us.

07:50.003 --> 07:51.805
-NADJA: Calm down.
-Really?

07:51.839 --> 07:53.507
How about now?

07:53.541 --> 07:55.375
-Been there, done that.
-JEFF: How about now?

07:55.408 --> 07:56.710
(roaring)

07:56.744 --> 07:59.847
(all screaming)

07:59.880 --> 08:01.348
NADJA:
Cut it out!

08:01.381 --> 08:03.651
-Would you stop it!?
-(chuckles)

08:03.684 --> 08:06.053
Pardon me, ghost.

08:06.086 --> 08:07.721
Later, man.
It was nice meeting you.

08:07.755 --> 08:10.524
So here's the situation.

08:10.558 --> 08:13.493
Every time my human ex-lover
is reincarnated,

08:13.527 --> 08:16.897
our bodies call to one another.

08:16.930 --> 08:20.734
But without a body,
he's all Jesk and no Gregor.

08:20.768 --> 08:22.135
And it stinks.

08:22.169 --> 08:25.238
My unfinished business,
how it torments me.

08:25.272 --> 08:29.242
-Please, help me complete it
so I may leave this plane.
-Sure.

08:29.276 --> 08:31.545
But what, exactly,
do you want me to do?

08:31.579 --> 08:34.214
Just, like, swear that
you'll help me...

08:34.247 --> 08:36.183
Do what?! No.
I don't have time for this.

08:36.216 --> 08:38.151
My husband is shitting himself
down the road.

08:38.185 --> 08:40.120
All right, all right.
I love you.

08:41.555 --> 08:43.691
-And a little to the left.
-(groans)

08:43.724 --> 08:46.493
-It sort of looks like updog.
-(hisses)

08:46.526 --> 08:49.262
(growls)
These ghosts, what are they?

08:49.296 --> 08:50.731
NADJA:
Humans have bodies.

08:50.764 --> 08:52.933
And within the body
resides the spirit.

08:52.966 --> 08:56.103
When the human dies,
the spirit is released.

08:56.136 --> 08:58.572
And that spirit is a ghost!

08:58.606 --> 09:01.274
We are all dead, technically.

09:01.308 --> 09:02.710
You, me and Laszlo.

09:02.743 --> 09:05.245
Each of us died
when we became vampires.

09:05.278 --> 09:07.080
Colin Robinson
I'm not so sure about.

09:07.114 --> 09:08.548
But the three of us.

09:08.582 --> 09:11.518
Yeah, I'm not positive
what my deal is either,

09:11.551 --> 09:14.087
so I just sort of
keep on truckin'.

09:14.121 --> 09:15.789
But what is the point?

09:15.823 --> 09:18.025
If we are technically dead,
like he says,

09:18.058 --> 09:19.226
could ghosts of us exist?

09:19.259 --> 09:22.095
No, but--

09:22.129 --> 09:23.430
Huh.

09:23.463 --> 09:26.800
-Hmm.
-Hmm.

09:26.834 --> 09:27.935
Huh...

09:27.968 --> 09:30.804
-Not now.
-Shut up.

09:30.838 --> 09:33.941
Hootorektas e-'pay' k-elastero

09:33.974 --> 09:35.809
kath-eye-restho

09:35.843 --> 09:37.144
hon-'pear' hootorektas

09:37.177 --> 09:41.114
e-'pay' k-elastero
apokatharet-eye.

09:41.148 --> 09:43.450
