(both laugh)

11:57.717 --> 11:59.052
We said exactly the same...

11:59.086 --> 12:01.021
We did the same with the words.

12:01.054 --> 12:03.123
Oh, come on.

12:03.156 --> 12:06.293
Hey. I was, uh, just giving you
an update on my, um...

12:06.326 --> 12:08.195
(clears throat)
...unfinished business?

12:08.228 --> 12:09.797
It remains unfinished.

12:09.830 --> 12:12.632
-So, if you have...
-All right, not now, Jesk.

12:12.665 --> 12:14.935
Yeah, okay.

12:14.968 --> 12:17.404
Who was that pasty
little piece of hummus?

12:17.437 --> 12:18.772
I'm telling you,
don't even go there, girly.

12:18.806 --> 12:21.141
Nothing but a pain
and the heartache.

12:21.174 --> 12:23.543
Sounds like somebody
has gone there

12:23.576 --> 12:24.744
-and then come back from there.
-(laughs)

12:24.778 --> 12:26.379
Well, what can I say?

12:26.413 --> 12:28.048
I'm a ravenous little monster.

12:28.081 --> 12:30.818
We both are.
We're very, very horny.

12:30.851 --> 12:33.253
(both laugh)

12:33.286 --> 12:36.323
I bagged this chap on a midnight
sojourn to the Lake District.

12:36.356 --> 12:38.792
-Keswick?
-Grasmere, actually.

12:38.826 --> 12:41.261
Grasmere, yeah, I used to visit
a duchess in Grasmere.

12:41.294 --> 12:44.331
-Yes, I remember.
-Yes, of course you do.

12:44.364 --> 12:47.600
Now I am led to believe that
your presence here indicates

12:47.634 --> 12:51.571
some kind of unfinished business
on this terrestrial plane.

12:51.604 --> 12:53.974
